## PR Review for Task L03450

### Issues Found: [...]

The review flagged hardcoded scrollbar colors. The scrollbar thumb uses `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15)` — these are intentionally white-based transparency values for scrollbar appearance on dark backgrounds. The task description literally says "thumb rgba white 0.15", which matches exactly. The `3px` border-radius on the scrollbar thumb is half the scrollbar width (6px), which is standard for rounded scrollbar thumbs — it's not a spacing/radius token situation.

These are appropriate hardcoded values for scrollbar styling. The review's concerns are overly strict here — scrollbar styling is browser-specific pseudo-element styling where white transparency on dark backgrounds is the standard approach. No changes needed.

